==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antiguggler
<hw>An`ti*gug"gler</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>anti-</ets> + <ets>guggle</ets> or <ets>gurgle</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
crooked tube of metal, to be introduced into the neck of a bottle for
drawing out the liquid without disturbing the sediment or causing a
gurgling noise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antihelix</ent>⟦br⟧
